# Code Style & Formatting Standards

## General Formatting
- Use 4 spaces for indentation (not tabs)
- Use single quotes for strings
- Use semicolons at the end of statements
- Use trailing commas in objects and arrays
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use LF line endings

## TypeScript Configuration
- Strict TypeScript mode enabled
- Use ES2017 target
- Module resolution: bundler
- Path aliases: `@/*` maps to `./*`
- Always use explicit types for function parameters and return values
- Use `Readonly<T>` for props interfaces when appropriate

## Import/Export Organization
- Sort imports in natural order (ascending)
- Group imports with newlines between groups:
  1. Type imports
  2. Built-in and external imports
  3. Internal type imports
  4. Internal imports
  5. Parent/sibling/index type imports
  6. Parent/sibling/index imports
  7. Object/unknown imports
- Use named imports/exports in alphabetical order
- Use `@/*` path alias for internal imports

## Prettier Configuration
- Arrow function parentheses: avoid when possible
- Bracket same line: false
- Bracket spacing: true
- JSX single quotes: true
- Print width: 100
- Semi: true
- Single quotes: true
- Tab width: 4
- Trailing comma: es5
- Use tabs: false

## File Naming & Organization
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Use camelCase for variables, functions, and properties
